subject.1030.response	## Threat: Unprotected AWS S3 Buckets ##\n\n**Description:** An AWS S3 bucket with default settings and no safeguards in place is publicly exposed to the Internet. This means that anyone who knows or guesses the bucket's URL can access, download, and possibly modify or delete the data it contains. \n\n**Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs):**\n- **Tactic(s):** Initial Access\n- **Technique(s):** T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing Application\n- **Procedure(s):** An attacker identifies the buckets public URL, accesses the unprotected bucket, downloads and analyses the data, and possibly modifies or deletes the data for malicious purposes.\n\n**Risk:**\n- **Attack Vector:** Network\n- **Attack Complexity:** Low\n- **Privileges Required:** None\n- **User Interaction:** None\n- **Social trends:** Trending\n- **Ease of exploitation:** High (Real-world)\n\n**Real-World Example:** In 2017, the Pentagon experienced a data breach due to an unprotected AWS S3 bucket that exposed 1.8 billion public internet posts collected over a period of 8 years.\n\n**Impact if Exploited:** The breach can lead to loss of confidentiality and integrity of data, damages to the company's reputation, and potential financial losses due to fines or lawsuits.\n\n**Threat Actor:** Cybercriminal\n\n**Attack Vector:** Publicly accessible URL\n\n**Detection and Response:** Monitor AWS CloudTrail logs for unusual access patterns or non-standard IP addresses. Set up AWS S3 bucket access logging to monitor requests. AWS GuardDuty can be used for threat detection.\n\n**Likelihood:** High\n\n**Dependencies:** The AWS S3 bucket must be publicly accessible and not have any safeguards in place.\n\n**Mitigation(s):**\n- Enable access control lists and bucket policies that restrict access to the S3 bucket.\n- Encrypt data at rest and in transit.\n- Regularly review and update permissions.\n\n**Log & Monitor:**\n- Monitor AWS CloudTrail logs.\n- Use AWS GuardDuty for threat detection.\n- Enable AWS S3 bucket access logging.	string	\N	2025-05-07 22:21:05.948425-05	2025-05-07 22:21:05.970763-05
